WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.240 --> 00:00:03.445
Good morning family, how are y'all doing today?

00:00:03.445 --> 00:00:09.950
Well, praise the Lord, I have Diana with me again and we are just excited to be here.

00:00:09.950 --> 00:00:34.446
You know, we're just seeking the Lord together and we've been reading this book by John Bevere, 'Drawing Near'.

00:00:34.446 --> 00:00:42.729
Yeah, it's amazing and it is phenomenal.

00:00:42.729 --> 00:01:02.578
We were just like scavengers, folks; we will look through wherever we can to find a good meal with the Lord.

00:01:03.733 --> 00:01:32.840
You know, if you don't feel like you're getting spiritually fed all the time in certain areas, you've got to find what it is.

00:01:32.840 --> 00:01:50.830
You can't just be lazy; you can't just depend on your pastor to feed you all the time.

00:01:50.830 --> 00:02:24.604
You've got to be bold enough and strong enough to go out there and say, 'Listen, I'm going to find me something today, whatever I need in my life.

00:02:24.604 --> 00:02:31.430
' Does that make sense?

00:02:31.430 --> 00:02:45.204
Yeah, not just on Wednesdays and Sundays—every day.

00:02:45.204 --> 00:02:48.947
Find something.

00:02:54.760 --> 00:03:26.130
You get your food on Sunday, you get your food on Wednesday, and if that's all you feed your spirit, your flesh eats every day, three times a day.

00:03:26.130 --> 00:04:03.613
If you feed your flesh two and three times a day, you need to feed your spirit, and you can't just feed it on Wednesdays and Sundays, right?

00:04:03.613 --> 00:04:19.845
So, Diana and I, we're always looking all the time for words that will fan the flame.

00:04:19.845 --> 00:04:31.310
How do you keep strong in these dark times?

00:04:46.063 --> 00:04:48.855
We had an election, and thank God it's over, but it's time to move on.

00:04:48.855 --> 00:05:05.450
I really believe the Holy Spirit is telling me, 'Brandon, let's not talk about politics no more.

00:05:05.450 --> 00:05:07.309
We're done.

00:05:07.309 --> 00:05:20.520
' We saw it, we had it, and the caravan's moving on, folks.

00:05:20.520 --> 00:05:34.862
I just can't park there no more; you'll dry up spiritually.

00:05:34.862 --> 00:05:44.795
Always praying for the election, always that stuff.

00:05:54.544 --> 00:06:11.740
Yeah, we pray for our government, we pray for our leaders, but we've got to get deeper in the things of God.

00:06:11.740 --> 00:06:44.405
I noticed even with this, I did my mission, I did what He said to do, and now He's telling me, 'Brandon, it's time for you to tell my people something different here.

00:06:44.405 --> 00:06:59.119
' Like we say, we came, we conquered; it's time to keep climbing.

00:06:59.119 --> 00:07:08.108
We don't build a tent there; we're climbers.

00:07:08.108 --> 00:07:18.740
So it's time to keep climbing, keep on pressing on.

00:07:18.740 --> 00:07:31.540
We've got to go to the summit, and I'm excited, y'all.

00:07:32.380 --> 00:08:07.702
You know, the Lord was instructing me about prayer, and He was talking about staying full, being filled and controlled by the Holy Spirit, but showing me examples of people who fake it a lot.

00:08:10.135 --> 00:08:39.919
You can fake being full for a season, for a little bit, and fool people because you have all the Christian lingo, the verbiage, the hallelujahs, the shouts, and you shake a little bit.

00:08:40.337 --> 00:09:00.870
You can put on a performance sometimes, and people fall for it.

00:09:00.870 --> 00:09:04.775
But if you're a seasoned veteran and you're watching that, you know the difference between fake and real.

00:09:11.395 --> 00:09:22.915
You know the difference between cold and hot, even whenever they pretend they're hot.

00:09:23.800 --> 00:09:43.299
You know when they start praying if there's no well there.

00:09:44.141 --> 00:10:09.095
I heard another person stand up before and they start praying, and the glory comes into the atmosphere.

00:10:09.095 --> 00:10:19.409
You can't mock the glory.

00:10:19.409 --> 00:10:33.884
When the glory is there, there's no flesh that can make that happen.

00:10:33.884 --> 00:10:58.347
It's beautiful when the spirit of the Lord comes in through prayer.

00:11:03.120 --> 00:11:19.577
It's Holy Ghost prayer versus somebody who is dry, trying to make prayer happen like a counterfeit.

00:11:19.577 --> 00:11:31.490
That's why we don't want that on our channel.

00:11:37.750 --> 00:11:40.173
I don't want to waste your time.

00:11:40.173 --> 00:11:43.460
If I don't feel it...

00:11:43.460 --> 00:12:16.405
there are some days I come here and I feel dry and I just try to get through, but I don't want that.

00:12:16.405 --> 00:12:57.270
I want to be filled with and controlled by the Holy Spirit so that when you take time out of your day, you're getting a fresh touch from the Holy Spirit.

00:13:09.835 --> 00:13:10.060
You walk away changed.

00:13:10.060 --> 00:13:44.610
I don't want to fall out in the Holy Ghost, shake a couple of times on the floor, and get up and be the same.

00:13:44.610 --> 00:13:49.315
No, I want impartation.

00:13:49.315 --> 00:13:54.555
I want to change.

00:13:55.079 --> 00:14:05.151
I want to go from glory to glory.

00:14:10.864 --> 00:14:55.019
I don't want to play church where we say a couple of whatever and we get up and we shake around and have a 'Holy Ghost thing' trying to mock what we had 10 years ago when we were kids.

00:15:04.337 --> 00:15:04.693
The Holy Spirit wasn't in it; it's just flesh.

00:15:12.149 --> 00:15:12.379
People get weird.

00:15:12.379 --> 00:15:36.799
I want something tangible, something I can bite my teeth into spiritually that's going to change me and draw me closer to Him.

00:15:46.101 --> 00:15:55.639
When we found this book by John Bevere, 'Drawing Near', it's exactly what we needed.

00:15:55.639 --> 00:16:08.680
He didn't sponsor this; we don't even know this man.

00:16:08.680 --> 00:16:17.333
We truly believe there's something in this.

00:16:17.333 --> 00:16:32.487
We've read a lot of his books and they're life-changing, very anointed.

00:16:32.487 --> 00:16:52.559
Some people say, 'Well, this is old,' but I don't care how old it is.

00:16:52.559 --> 00:17:02.627
I'm extremely picky about what I read.

00:17:02.627 --> 00:17:19.080
Diana will read a couple of pages and she'll go, 'This is trash,' and throw it away.

00:17:19.080 --> 00:17:32.880
A lot of people send us books and she'll throw them away.

00:17:44.975 --> 00:17:52.190
If you don't want to have your feelings hurt, don't tell her to read your book because we're not going to sugarcoat it.

00:18:00.200 --> 00:18:00.410
You can't counterfeit the Holy Spirit.

00:18:00.410 --> 00:18:06.479
We're veterans, folks, and I'm not trying to be prideful, but I'm a veteran when it comes to knowing what's real and authentic.

00:18:06.479 --> 00:18:11.977
I know it instantaneously.

00:18:14.406 --> 00:18:17.320
I'm like a tractor beam.

00:18:29.024 --> 00:18:29.316
I just know when you know.

00:18:29.316 --> 00:18:50.270
Even when you see people behind the pulpit, you listen to them and go, 'You just need to sit down.

00:18:50.270 --> 00:19:29.720
' I'm not trying to be rude, but you're wasting people's time if you didn't take the time to fill yourself up with the Holy Ghost before you came to church.

00:19:29.720 --> 00:19:37.720
Sit down and pass the baton to somebody else.

00:19:37.720 --> 00:19:45.907
I want to go from glory to glory.

00:19:53.453 --> 00:20:16.150
We get all caught up in the politics and everything going on and we camp there, but God's wanting to move the caravan and go up the mountain now.

00:20:16.150 --> 00:20:43.226
We've got to pray for this nation, yes, but we've got to get a harvest for the Kingdom; He is the Lord of the harvest.

00:20:43.226 --> 00:21:03.159
You can always tell when a book is written for money or if it's really Holy Spirit inspired.

00:21:04.404 --> 00:21:20.844
I don't want to cut you off, Diana, I'm sorry; I start rattling too much.

00:21:21.173 --> 00:21:27.332
I want you to show them, babe.

00:21:30.039 --> 00:21:32.714
This is what changes you.

00:21:32.714 --> 00:21:42.059
Aren't you ready for some authentic, quit-playing-church folks?

00:21:42.059 --> 00:21:59.497
I'm tired of walking away and not having a life-experience change with the Lord.

00:22:06.036 --> 00:22:28.546
I don't want to just fall down and shake a little bit; I want to get up and go, 'My God, I'm changed.

00:22:28.546 --> 00:23:03.035
' You get lackadaisical and comfortable as you're praying for the election and all that stuff, but you always have to come back to the heartbeat of God.

00:23:09.874 --> 00:23:12.552
What is He saying about this generation?

00:23:12.552 --> 00:23:15.640
Draw near.

00:23:15.640 --> 00:23:23.480
I'm desperate for a touch today.

00:23:23.480 --> 00:23:47.672
I see the emails and you're so broken; you're not getting fed at your churches.

00:23:47.672 --> 00:24:18.440
You're desperate for change, for your marriages, for healing, for all this stuff, but you're not going to the Source.

00:24:18.440 --> 00:24:27.200
It's about drawing near to Him.

00:24:27.200 --> 00:24:34.176
It's being like Moses.

00:24:34.176 --> 00:25:08.316
He had everything in Egypt, just like John Bevere talks about in his book, and he never once complained about wanting to go back.

00:25:08.316 --> 00:25:40.164
He even said, 'I don't want to go to the Promised Land, I don't want to go to the next level, if You're not going with us.

00:25:40.432 --> 00:25:56.789
I would rather stay here in the desert if I don't have You.

00:25:56.789 --> 00:26:10.200
' He chose the desert just to stay with God.

00:26:21.973 --> 00:26:26.579
That's desperate, because the desert is not a fun place.

00:26:36.908 --> 00:27:08.373
I don't think a lot of people want to go through any hard times—a financial collapse or any craziness—because anytime I bring it up, people say, 'Oh my God, I rebuke that.

00:27:08.373 --> 00:27:35.780
' But the Lord said to keep doing the same thing and asking for something different is insanity.

00:27:35.780 --> 00:27:47.360
We want change, we want the glory, we want revival.

00:27:47.360 --> 00:28:03.150
I had a mega-minister text me tonight asking, 'Where's the glory?

00:28:03.150 --> 00:28:04.229
Why haven't we seen it?

00:28:04.229 --> 00:28:07.119
What's the hold-up?

00:28:07.119 --> 00:28:13.840
' That's a great question.

00:28:13.840 --> 00:28:19.634
Where is the revival?

00:28:19.634 --> 00:28:28.389
Where is the presence of the Lord in the churches?

00:28:28.389 --> 00:28:37.747
Do you know of anything real happening?

00:28:37.747 --> 00:29:03.756
We had something at the tent revival a couple of weeks ago, but I haven't heard of anything since we focused on the election.

00:29:03.756 --> 00:29:29.880
We got what we wanted, and now we have the ability to turn around, but we don't want to change.

00:29:29.880 --> 00:29:52.908
They don't want to let go of their seeker-friendly message with skinny jeans and fog machines.

00:29:52.908 --> 00:29:59.650
They're like Moses's people—they choose to stay back.

00:29:59.650 --> 00:30:44.164
Moses went up on the mountain for 40 days, and they all had the ability to come up with him; the Lord invited every single one of them to have a relationship with Him.

00:31:00.520 --> 00:31:00.800
But they chose to send Moses because it was uncomfortable to their flesh.

00:31:00.800 --> 00:31:03.705
Aaron didn't go.

00:31:03.705 --> 00:31:25.1000
Joshua had more fear of the Lord; he stood down there, wanting to be as close as he could.

00:31:31.585 --> 00:31:36.036
In Exodus, it says He drew them all there to have a relationship with Him.

00:31:36.036 --> 00:31:42.075
He's doing the same thing today.

00:31:42.075 --> 00:31:45.960
He's no respecter of persons; He wants a relationship with every single one of you.

00:31:45.960 --> 00:31:50.720
We are like sponges, folks.

00:31:50.720 --> 00:31:54.760
What you feed on the most is what's going to come out of you.

00:31:59.016 --> 00:32:15.019
I can tell a lot of times when we go around people, they don't have any Holy Ghost because they avoid the conversation.

00:32:15.019 --> 00:32:31.308
An exchange takes place over meals that is greater than in any other setting.

00:32:31.308 --> 00:32:56.000
This is why Paul tells us not to eat with someone who claims to be a believer yet lives in habitual sin—that's 1 Corinthians 5:11.

00:32:56.000 --> 00:33:06.440
We open our heart and become intimate over a meal.

00:33:06.440 --> 00:33:33.910
When people invite us out and get offended when we say no, it's not that I'm better than them; it's in 1 Corinthians.

00:33:33.910 --> 00:33:40.000
Diana, read that scripture.

00:33:40.000 --> 00:34:33.335
'But now I am writing to you that you must not associate with anyone who claims to be a brother or sister but is sexually immoral or greedy, an idolator or slanderer, a drunkard or swindler.

00:34:39.879 --> 00:34:40.840
Do not even eat with such people.

00:34:40.840 --> 00:34:47.920
' You've got to come up higher; be careful who you eat with.

00:34:56.457 --> 00:35:04.940
Jesus would go out and hang out with people, but He dominated the atmosphere.

00:35:04.940 --> 00:35:09.960
If you're not strong enough to dominate the atmosphere, don't hang around them because they'll influence you.

00:35:09.960 --> 00:35:16.771
You need to change atmospheres.

00:35:16.771 --> 00:35:32.583
I can feel the atmosphere through discernment and words of knowledge.

00:35:48.520 --> 00:35:49.040
I know if a pastor is dry or lukewarm.

00:35:49.040 --> 00:35:50.004
You can't fake it.

00:35:50.004 --> 00:35:56.484
We seek out where it's authentic.

00:35:56.484 --> 00:36:06.692
Here's another piece of the book I wanted her to read.

00:36:12.380 --> 00:36:50.367
The Holy Spirit told him to pull off the side of the road and whisper to his heart: 'Did I not say to you, pray without ceasing?

00:36:50.367 --> 00:36:59.008
' He responded, 'Yes Lord.

00:36:59.008 --> 00:37:09.053
' He probed further: 'Is prayer a monologue or dialogue?

00:37:09.053 --> 00:37:19.870
' He responded, 'It's a dialogue, Lord.

00:37:19.870 --> 00:37:53.593
' His words came quick: 'Well, if I said to pray without ceasing, then that means I am willing to communicate with you without ceasing.

00:37:53.593 --> 00:38:13.159
' The more you get to know a person, the more you learn their ways.

00:38:22.000 --> 00:38:22.230
It's the same with the Father.

00:38:32.371 --> 00:38:37.687
The more you draw near to Him, the more you know when something is bothering Him.

00:38:37.687 --> 00:38:52.240
I know when I've overstepped a line and need to apologize.

00:38:52.240 --> 00:39:06.319
I want to be quick to repent and follow the Holy Spirit.

00:39:06.319 --> 00:39:13.725
The Bible says He corrects those He loves.

00:39:22.791 --> 00:39:23.187
I want to grow.

00:39:25.836 --> 00:39:36.847
I don't want the next four years to be more of the same road.

00:39:43.176 --> 00:39:45.649
I'm ready for Him to come.

00:39:45.649 --> 00:39:52.707
But we have to have major changes.

00:39:52.707 --> 00:40:00.1000
It might make your flesh squirm.

00:40:00.1000 --> 00:40:20.079
People don't want a financial crisis, but the Lord is concerned about the unbeliever.

00:40:26.804 --> 00:40:43.060
What is it going to take to get the people in San Francisco, Portland, and Seattle to awaken?

00:40:46.800 --> 00:40:51.280
What draws them to repentance?

00:40:51.280 --> 00:41:30.183
Sometimes it takes a shake, like COVID did, to awaken the people in China or those who have cried out to Buddha or Muhammad and still don't have an answer.

00:41:30.183 --> 00:41:40.280
They need us to be the salt and light.

00:41:40.973 --> 00:41:54.114
The only way you'll get that is by drawing near.

00:41:54.114 --> 00:42:14.370
It's not politics; it's not Donald Trump; it's not the Senate or the House.

00:42:15.750 --> 00:42:29.380
The only thing that's going to change America is an awakening unto God.

00:42:29.380 --> 00:42:47.996
People get mad when I talk about a shaking, but I want what He wants.

00:42:47.996 --> 00:43:16.240
Jesus didn't want to die on the cross in His flesh; He sweat drops of blood, but He said, 'Not my will, but Yours be done.

00:43:16.240 --> 00:43:30.245
' What will it take to wake up the billions going to hell?

00:43:30.245 --> 00:43:39.138
They are comfortable in Las Vegas or the clubs.

00:43:43.840 --> 00:43:48.607
It's going to take something drastic.

00:43:59.096 --> 00:43:59.354
We're going to pray for the lost.

00:44:02.215 --> 00:44:15.080
I want revival and a harvest, but not at the expense of making our flesh comfortable.

00:44:18.867 --> 00:44:22.695
The glory comes with a price.

00:44:22.695 --> 00:44:28.910
Are you willing to pay it?

00:44:28.910 --> 00:44:34.914
It takes dying to self.

00:44:37.697 --> 00:44:48.359
The Lord even told Diana He's waiting on the harvesters.

00:44:48.359 --> 00:44:58.369
Tell them what the Lord told you, babe.

00:44:58.369 --> 00:45:39.943
'See, this is the problem with My body; they are so afraid of hearing the wrong voice that they don't even want to hear My voice at all, so they shut it all off.

00:45:39.943 --> 00:46:02.103
But if you're spending time in the word and seeking Me, you will hear it.

00:46:02.103 --> 00:46:06.990
' The enemy's goal is separation.

00:46:06.990 --> 00:46:21.966
People are afraid of the prayer language because they're stuck in their heads.

00:46:21.966 --> 00:46:43.280
If you spend time with Him and feed on the word, the rest will fall into place.

00:46:43.280 --> 00:46:56.660
If you can't hear God for yourself, you're in trouble.

00:46:56.660 --> 00:47:27.000
A seasoned person familiar with His voice doesn't have to test everything every single second because they know Him.

00:47:27.000 --> 00:47:38.800
It should always be backed by scripture.

00:47:38.800 --> 00:47:55.089
If I can't find it in the word, it ain't God.

00:47:55.089 --> 00:48:10.914
He's passionate about a relationship with you.

00:48:10.914 --> 00:48:27.303
Even the hang-up on Christmas—Jesus is the reason for the season.

00:48:47.595 --> 00:48:47.950
We celebrate Jesus.

00:48:47.950 --> 00:49:09.244
Some say Easter is pagan, too, but I celebrate anytime I can give God glory.

00:49:25.469 --> 00:49:27.931
We're not talking about some pagan entity; we're talking about 'Joy to the World'.

00:49:29.545 --> 00:49:31.138
I give gifts when the Lord says to.

00:49:31.138 --> 00:49:47.853
One year when we had nothing, someone gave us $1,000 for Christmas.

00:49:47.853 --> 00:50:16.200
People are so scared there's a devil behind every bush that they let people rob them of something joyous.

00:50:16.200 --> 00:50:43.057
If you don't want to follow the channel because I have a 'pagan tree', then bye.

00:50:43.057 --> 00:50:46.790
I'm determined to have a relationship with the Father.

00:51:06.173 --> 00:51:06.515
We seek deeper intimacy.

00:51:10.168 --> 00:51:13.891
I make an atmosphere for Him.

00:51:13.891 --> 00:51:48.940
If He showed up at your house, would He want to stay, or is there so much strife and crap?

00:51:48.940 --> 00:51:55.903
We're trying to fan your flame.

00:51:55.903 --> 00:52:15.235
We want to inspire you to be on fire.

00:52:15.235 --> 00:52:30.303
We see the emails and have compassion.

00:52:42.070 --> 00:52:45.253
I feel like I'm in an emergency ward.

00:52:45.253 --> 00:53:02.860
You're on spiritual life support and you need living water.

00:53:02.860 --> 00:53:09.903
Diana, read about the sand.

00:53:09.903 --> 00:53:24.630
His thoughts about you outnumber the grains of sand.

00:53:40.666 --> 00:53:41.133
Our value is determined by the purchaser.

00:53:41.133 --> 00:53:49.771
What is our value to God?

00:53:49.771 --> 00:53:58.302
That's where we find our true value.

00:53:58.302 --> 00:54:06.480
God sets the standard, not men.

00:54:15.667 --> 00:54:25.409
I encourage you to get the book; there are nuggets that will fan your flame.

00:54:31.071 --> 00:54:34.805
We pray for you.

00:54:34.805 --> 00:54:42.040
There is a great shaking coming.

00:54:42.040 --> 00:55:16.689
There will be days that seem dark, but there will be light in Goshen, folks, and we will have the greater glory.

00:55:16.689 --> 00:55:37.753
I told you there would be a reprieve, but when will the house of cards fall?

00:55:37.753 --> 00:55:52.400
There's too much debt; there has to be a reset.

00:55:52.400 --> 00:56:07.268
We're going to pray for the Lord to fan your flame.

00:56:07.268 --> 00:56:17.560
Father, we thank You for every person here.

00:56:21.160 --> 00:56:29.459
We call for a hunger to grow inside of them.

00:56:29.459 --> 00:56:39.413
We take authority over satanic forces and addictions.

00:56:53.694 --> 00:56:53.979
We thank You for a supernatural transfer.

00:57:00.830 --> 00:57:06.572
We thank You for books like this from John Bevere.

00:57:16.435 --> 00:57:17.920
We want to go from glory to glory.

00:57:33.275 --> 00:57:38.850
We lift up Elon Musk—this is day three—and we call him born again in the name of Jesus.

00:57:38.850 --> 00:57:54.316
According to Ephesians 1:18, let the eyes of his understanding be enlightened.

00:57:54.316 --> 00:58:02.039
Give him a supernatural encounter.

00:58:02.039 --> 00:58:10.286
Let him be the next Billy Graham.

00:58:10.286 --> 00:58:20.319
Let him use technology like Starlink for the gospel.

00:58:20.319 --> 00:59:07.000
We believe that for Elon Musk today, that he'll use that technology all for the glory of the living God, and Father, we believe it in Jesus' name.

00:59:19.147 --> 00:59:25.455
We love the good emails—like the one from the lady involved in the motorcycle accident.

00:59:25.455 --> 00:59:31.834
It's an honor that you watch.

00:59:35.951 --> 00:59:36.599
We've made it 30 days.

00:59:36.599 --> 00:59:40.716
God bless you all.

00:59:40.716 --> 00:59:41.635
Bye-bye.
